# Privacy Policy — SpinGo

**Effective date:** July 5, 2026

SpinGo ("the App", "we") is an activity bingo app for couples and friends. We built it to work entirely on your device — the App has no server, no accounts, and no analytics. This policy explains what data the App handles, why, and what your rights are.

---

## 1. The Short Version

- **No account required.** The App works without registration — we never ask for your name, email address, or any other personal details.
- **Completely offline.** The App makes no network connections. Nothing you enter ever leaves your device.
- **No analytics, no crash reporting, no advertising trackers.** We do not use any third-party tracking, analytics, or advertising SDKs.
- **Your photos stay on your phone.** Photos you attach to completed activities are stored only in the App's local storage.

---

## 2. Data We Do Not Collect

We do not collect, request, transmit, or store on any server:

- Names, email addresses, phone numbers, or postal addresses
- GPS or location data
- Contacts or files on your device
- Usage statistics or analytics events
- Advertising identifiers (IDFA) — the App does not request App Tracking Transparency permission because it does not track you

---

## 3. Data Stored Only on Your Device

Everything you create in SpinGo is stored **locally on your device only**:

- Your bingo boards, activities, and completion dates
- Comments and notes you add to completed activities
- Photos you attach to completed activities

This data never leaves your phone. It is deleted when you uninstall the App, and you can also delete it at any time from within the App's settings.

### 3.1 Camera and Photo Library Access

The App asks for permission to use your **camera** or **photo library** only when you choose to attach a photo to a completed activity. The selected or captured photo is copied into the App's private local storage. The App never reads other photos in your library, and photos are never uploaded anywhere.

---

## 4. Why There Is No Legal Basis Section

Because the App does not transmit or process any personal data outside your device, we do not process personal data within the meaning of Art. 4 GDPR. All data remains under your sole control on your device.

---

## 5. Data Sharing

We do **not sell** or share any data — we never receive any in the first place.

---

## 6. Data Retention

All data is under your control:

- Delete individual photos or memories within the App
- Reset all data via the App's settings
- Uninstall the App to remove everything

---

## 7. Your Rights

Under the GDPR you have the right to access, rectify, erase, or restrict the processing of personal data, the right to object, and the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority. Since we do not hold any data about you, there is nothing we could look up, hand over, or delete on our side — all your data lives exclusively on your device.

---

## 8. Children

SpinGo does not collect personal data from anyone, including children. The App is suitable for general audiences.

---

## 9. Changes to This Policy

If we add features in the future that change how data is handled (for example, optional sync or sharing features), we will update this policy before those features launch and indicate the new effective date at the top of this page.

